=====================================================================
			31st December 2020
=====================================================================
Android ndk21 uses the clang compiler. The original valgrind code was
written for gcc. Due to this, patches are needed to compile valgrind
for aarch64-android using the clang compiler.
=====================================================================

Bug1 : Compiler Error: __builtin_ setjmp and longjmp not found

Fix  : Define the functions setjmp and longjmp for ARM64 in the file 
       coregrind/m_libcsetjmp.c and include/pub_tool_libcsetjmp.h

Patch: patch_libcsetjumpH.patch patch_libcsetjumpC.patch

Urls : https://kde-bugs-dist.kde.narkive.com/RcgbC0xA

=====================================================================

Bug2 : Linker Error: Undefined reference to __aeabi_memcpy4 
       __aeabi_memcpy8 __aeabi_memclr8

Fix  : Add definitions for the following functions in the file
       coregrind/m_main.c

Patch: patch_aeabi.patch

Urls : https://kde-bugs-dist.kde.narkive.com/KPgskUaa

=====================================================================

Bug3 : Redefinition of struct Elf32_Nhdr

Fix  : As it is already defined in libc, comment out the definition
       from coregrind/m_coredump/coredump-elf.c

Patch: patch_elf.patch

=====================================================================
